qas.question: An ARM architecture computer can be found in what?

answers.text: a PDA or a hand-held videogame

context: Machine languages and the assembly languages that represent them (collectively termed low-level programming languages) tend to be unique to a particular type of computer. For instance, an ARM architecture computer (such as may be found in <a0_0>a PDA or a hand-held videogame<a0_0/>) cannot understand the machine language of an Intel Pentium or the AMD Athlon 64 computer that might be in a PC.
